As shown in Fig. 1, the PV cell model is a single-diode model because it is built on the assumption that the recombination failure in the depletion area is negligible. The loss of the P–N junction’s depletion area is important, which is invisible in the single-diode configuration. The basic equation of semiconductor diode theory represents the characteristics of an ideal PV cell as follows9,13:Figure 1
