The lack of recombination that is ignored in the single–diode model causes the inaccuracy of the PV model parameters. Therefore, the double-diode model is chosen to represent the physical form of the PV cell, as shown in Fig. 2. A precise model is achieved by considering recombination loss. The diffusion current is focused in the p–n junction material by using one of the double diodes, and the other is added to account for recombination loss20,21. Hence, the PV module output current can be defined as:Figure 2
